The Financial Times/Stock Exchange indexof Britain's 100 leading shares fell by its largest ever marginin points terms during a single session, dropping 46.1 to closeat 2,002.5. The index earlier today touched a low of 1,993.7.    Before today the largest one day points decline was a 35.8point drop on February 9.    The index fall was triggered by fears a trade war couldbreak out with Japan following news the U.S. Increased tariffson Japanese imports after the breakdown of a 1986 semiconductorpact. Today's sharp sell off at the Wall Street opening gaveselling momentum to a market which was already at its lows. REUTER&#3;